{
  "texts": [
    "Specifically, the method follows the concept that different shots cannot be reconstructed with the learned dictionary, i.e., each shot in the video needs to learn the dictionary corresponding with it.",
    "After determining the shot boundaries, a representative keyframe is selected from each shot.",
    "This method is shown to be the powerful keyframe-extraction algorithm on VSUMM and YouTube datasets.",
    "Ma et al. [27] noticed that the sparse subset selectionbased algorithms proposed in the past do not consider local or global relationships between frames.",
    "Therefore, the authors' proposed a similarity-based block sparse subset-selection method."
  ]
}